title: Bullpadel Vertex 04 Padel Racket
description: The new Bullpadel Vertex 04 is a diamond-shaped racket with a rough Top Spin surface which offers maximum power. It is designed for professional or advanced players. It incorporates two new frame concepts. The CURVAKTIV system: its rotated structure provides resistance against twisting. Thanks to the rotation of its surfaces, we can introduce a variable section on the side of the racket. We have managed to introduce a smaller section than that of the vertex03 frame, increasing rigidity, but we have also managed to widen the section lengthwise, achieving a more uniform transmission of stresses throughout the racket. This improved distribution of vibrations and stresses is also supported by the combination of the CURVAKTIV with the AIR POWER. The AIR POWER is the natural evolution of the Air React Channel system. It is a channel that we create using a hollow area in the lower side of the blade. This hollow area works better than if it were a solid piece because it is made up of less material and is less prone to deformation, making the structure stronger. The external core is made from Xtend Carbon 12k carbon, its internal core from the new MultiEva rubber, and its frame from 100% carbon fibre CarbonTube. It has a CustomWeight plate system, allowing for balance of the racket to be modified according to the needs of every player. It offers a Vibradrive system for absorption of vibrations. It also incorporates the Hesacore grip that reduces effort, vibrations, and the probability of injury.

Built with a diamond-shaped head, it features a durable Polyglass fiberglass surface and a soft EvaLastic rubber core, offering a responsive and comfortable hitting experience. Its CarbonTube frame, made from 100% carbon fiber, ensures lasting strength, while the Vertex heart design helps distribute weight evenly and reduce vibrations for maximum shot power.

Train like a pro and play with confidence using the Vertex 03 JR W!

Key Specifications:

  • Weight: 335 – 345 grams

  • Head Shape: Diamond

  • Balance: Medium

  • Beam Width: 35 mm

  • Core: EvaLastic

  • Frame: CarbonTube (100% carbon)

  • Surface: Polyglass

  • Player Level: Advanced Junior

Technology Highlights:

  • Carbontube: Reinforced 100% carbon frame for durability and control

  • Polyglass: High-resistance fiberglass surface that balances flexibility and strength

  • Vertex Heart: Optimizes weight distribution and minimizes vibration

  • EvaLastic: Soft core providing excellent comfort, feel, and long-lasting performance

title: AT10 LUXURY GENIUS 12K ALUM XTREM 2026 BY AGUSTÍN TAPIA
description:
The AT10 12K Alum XTREM 2026 has been designed alongside Agustín Tapia for players seeking a firmer feel and the perfect balance between power and control.

We’ve updated the mould, and in terms of technological innovation, it features the key highlights of the new AT10 collection: the Weight Balance counterweight system to adjust the racket’s balance, Chromic Paint reactive finish and the Dual Spin surface, which maximises spin generation. This model incorporates the new 12K Alum Xtrem carbon, providing a stiffer feel on impact, greater durability and consistent performance even under significant temperature changes.

title: AT10 LUXURY GENIUS 18K ALUM 2026 BY AGUSTÍN TAPIA
description:
The new AT10 Genius 18K Alum for the 2026 season raises the bar in innovation, evolving the racket with which Agustín Tapia reached the pinnacle of world padel with a new mould. This year, the racket used by the “Mozart of Catamarca” features the revolutionary Weight Balance counterweight system, allowing you to adjust the racket’s balance to your playing style for a fully personalised experience.

A major aesthetic innovation is the Chromic Paint, a reactive finish in the core that synchronises with the rubber colour, creating a harmonious and striking appearance on court. Additionally, the new Dual Spin surface combines 3D texture and a silica sand finish across the racket face, maximising spin generation without compromising material durability.

title: AT10 LUXURY GENIUS ATTACK 12K ALUM XTREM 2026 BY AGUSTÍN TAPIA
description:
The AT10 12K Alum XTREM Attack 2026 has been developed alongside Agustín Tapia for aggressive players seeking maximum power with a solid, firm feel on every shot.

Its diamond shape, high balance and longer grip offer offensive play without compromising control. It features the key innovations of the new AT10 collection: the Weight Balance counterweight system, allowing personalised racket balance, Chromic Paint reactive finish and the Dual Spin surface, which enhances spin generation.

In addition to a redesigned mould, it debuts the new 12K Alum Xtrem Carbon, an exclusive NOX development that provides greater stiffness, a finer and more uniform surface, increased durability and stable performance even under
extreme temperature changes.

title: AT10 LUXURY GENIUS ATTACK 18K ALUM 2026 BY AGUSTÍN TAPIA
description:
The new AT10 Genius Attack 18K Alum 2026 comes revamped for aggressive players looking for maximum power without losing precision. With its diamond format, high balance and longer grip, it is the perfect racket to dominate the offensive game.

This season, we’ve redesigned it with an improved mould, and the standout innovation is the Weight Balance counterweight system, allowing you to adjust the balance to your preference. The racket also features the innovative Chromic Paint in the core, which reacts to light and changes colour, along with the Dual Spin surface to maximise spin. Combined with the 18K aluminised carbon structure and the MLD Black Eva core, it ensures a solid, comfortable feel and consistent performance in any playing condition.

title: ML10 VENTUS CONTROL 3K BY MIGUEL LAMPERTI
description:
The ML10 Ventus Control 3K, Miguel Lamperti’s new ally, arrives with a new mould to take one of padel’s most iconic models to the next level. Recognised for two consecutive years by Testea as the best control racket, this version marks a true revolution of a classic.

Its round shape and balanced weight distribution provide a wide sweet spot for absolute control on every shot—ideal for dictating the pace of play and building points in your favour.

With 3K carbon fibre on the faces and an HR3 Colour EVA core, the ML10 Ventus Control delivers exceptional feel, stability and excellent ball rebound, even during the most demanding rallies.

title: EA10 VENTUS ATTACK 12K XTREM BY EDU ALONSO
description:
The EA10 Ventus Attack 12K XTREM, designed in collaboration with Edu Alonso, is designed for players looking to dominate the attacking game and make every shot count. It features the new mould from the 2026 Luxury racket collection, which improves aerodynamics and overall performance.

Its diamond shape, longer grip and high attacking balance allow for powerful shots while maintaining the precision needed to control the decisive moments of the match. The combination of 12K Xtrem carbon on the faces and the MLD Black Eva core guarantees a firm feel, excellent ball rebound and stability even during the most demanding rallies.

title: EA10 VENTUS HYBRID 12K XTREM BY EDU ALONSO
description:
Designed together with Edu Alonso, one of the most outstanding young Spaniards on the professional circuit, the EA10 Ventus Hybrid 12K XTREM is designed for players who experience padel with maximum energy during every point. With its teardrop shape and perfect balance, this racket responds with agility on fast shots and offers the power and control needed to adapt to any situation. It features the new mould from the Signature Racket collection, which improves aerodynamics and overall performance, providing a more responsive and precise playing experience.﻿

Manageable and versatile, the EA10 Ventus Hybrid is the ideal racket for players who, like Edu Alonso, are looking for fast and dynamic play and are ready to dominate the court at all times.

title: AT10 LUXURY GENIUS 12K ALUM XTREM LITE 2026 BY AGUSTÍN TAPIA
description:
The AT10 12K Alum XTREM Lite 2026 has been developed alongside Agustín Tapia for players seeking the perfect balance of power, control and greater lightness in their game. Weighing between 355 and 365 grams, this racket offers superior manoeuvrability without compromising the characteristic performance of the AT10 range.

It features the new 2026 Luxury series mould and key innovations such as the Weight Balance counterweight system and the Dual Spin surface to maximise spin on every shot. Its 12K Alum Xtrem carbon construction provides stiffness, durability and stability even under temperature changes, all in a lighter, more agile version for dynamic and precise play.

title: VENTUS HYBRID 12K LITE
description:
The Ventus Hybrid 12K Lite is designed for players seeking the perfect balance between control and power, with greater manoeuvrability thanks to its reduced weight of 355–365g. It features the new mould from the 2026 Luxury racket collection, which improves aerodynamics and overall performance.﻿

Its teardrop shape and medium balance provide an agile, versatile response, ideal for adapting to any match situation. Built with a carbon frame, MLD Black Eva core, and 12K carbon fibre faces, it delivers a firm feel, excellent ball rebound and outstanding stability even during the most demanding points.

title: VK10 VENTUS CONTROL 12K BY ARANZAZU OSORO
description:
﻿The VK10 Ventus 12K Control, designed in collaboration with Aranzazu Osoro, is designed for players who fight every point with intensity and seek to dominate the court with intelligence and precision. It features the new mould from the 2026 Luxury racket collection, which improves aerodynamics and overall performance.﻿

The new racket from “La Vikinga” offers absolute control and a wide sweet spot, ideal for managing the pace of the match and responding with confidence on every shot. It has 12K carbon on the faces and an MLD Black Eva core, providing firmness, stability and great ball output.

title: AT10 PRO CUP SOFT BY AGUSTÍN TAPIA
description:
The AT Pro Cup Soft 2026 evolves with the mould of Agustín Tapia’s 2025 racket, incorporating advanced technologies such as the EOS Flap, which improves aerodynamics and manoeuvrability, and the Pulse System, designed to reduce vibrations and maximise comfort on every shot.

Designed for players who prioritise comfort, this racket combines aluminised fibreglass with an HR3 Soft EVA core, delivering a medium-firm feel that provides precision without sacrificing excellent ball rebound.

title: AT10 PRO CUP HARD BY AGUSTÍN TAPIA
description:
The new AT10 Pro Cup HARD 2026 updates its design while maintaining the essence of an iconic racket, now featuring the mould used by Agustín Tapia in 2025. It incorporates the latest high-performance innovations such as the EOS Flap, which enhances aerodynamics and manoeuvrability, and the Pulse System, which reduces vibrations for a more comfortable and stable game.

Designed for players who prioritise power, this racket combines an aluminised fibreglass structure with a metallic finish for greater reactivity, along with the HR3 hard EVA core, delivering a firm feel and powerful ball rebound.

title: EQUATION SOFT ADVANCED
description:
The EQUATION Soft 2026 offers a softer feel thanks to its specialised core, designed for players who prefer greater ball rebound and a more comfortable strike, especially during long or intense sessions.

Like its standard version, it maintains a medium balance, carbon frame and anti-vibration system, helping to reduce the risk of injury without compromising performance.

The rough Exclusive Spin faces enhance spin generation, while the Smartstrap® system allows the safety cord to be easily replaced, making it more hygienic, secure and customisable.

title: EQUATION HARD ADVANCED
description:
The EQUATION Hard maintains its renowned combination of manoeuvrability, control and precision, offering excellent feel and a wide sweet spot thanks to the rubber also used in competition rackets.

With medium balance, a carbon frame, and an anti-vibration system, it is designed to protect the player from potential injuries without compromising performance.

Its faces feature rough Exclusive Spin, which enhances spin generation on every shot. It also includes the Smartstrap® replaceable safety cord system, making it more hygienic, safer and fully customisable.

title: X-ZERO BLUE
description:
The X-Zero is the perfect racket for beginners and intermediate players looking for superior control and greater forgiveness on every shot.

Its round shape and new optimised hole pattern widen the sweet spot, improving ball placement and reducing errors on off-centre hits.

A racket designed to offer confidence from day one, helping you to improve your technique and enjoy every game more.

title: X-HERO WHITE
description:
The X-Hero is the ideal racket for beginner and intermediate players looking for a balance between consistency, comfort and manoeuvrability to enjoy every match or training session.

Its round shape and state-of-the-art materials guarantee maximum control in every shot, offering a dynamic and fun experience on the court.

It incorporates technologies from higher ranges, such as the HR3 rubber core for improved power and feel, a carbon frame that provides strength and stability and 3K fibreglass faces that optimise ball rebound.
 

Available in white, red and blue
